\newlabel{sec:supp}{{6}{21}{Supplementary Figures}{section*.16}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Supplementary Figure S1. Left: Device wear time over the seven-day home monitoring period, shown as violin plots with jittered subject points for POMS and healthy controls. Median wear time is 59 hours for POMS and 53 hours for healthy controls, with no significant group difference (Mann-Whitney $U$, $p = 0.19$). Right: Per-subject median bout duration by cohort (one data point per subject). Medians are 14 s for both groups, with POMS showing a wider lower tail\relax }}{21}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:supp_wear_median_bout}{{8}{21}{Supplementary Figure S1. Left: Device wear time over the seven-day home monitoring period, shown as violin plots with jittered subject points for POMS and healthy controls. Median wear time is 59 hours for POMS and 53 hours for healthy controls, with no significant group difference (Mann-Whitney $U$, $p = 0.19$). Right: Per-subject median bout duration by cohort (one data point per subject). Medians are 14 s for both groups, with POMS showing a wider lower tail\relax }{figure.caption.17}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Supplementary Figure S2. Sensitivity of home 6MWD prediction MAE to the minimum walking-bout duration threshold. At each threshold (10, 30, 60, 120, 240 s) the cached per-bout features are filtered, re-aggregated, combined with the 29 whole-recording activity features, and fed to the headline Bout+Act-Top20+Demo pipeline (Ridge $\alpha =20$, leave-one-out cross-validation). Error bars are 95\% percentile bootstrap confidence intervals (B = 2000). The 10\,s threshold yields the best MAE of 56.0\,m; stricter thresholds reduce the number of usable bouts (mean bouts per subject drop from 1{,}454 at 10\,s to 11 at 240\,s) and at 240\,s leave 9 of 101 subjects with zero bouts, degrading MAE to 65.5\,m.\relax }}{21}{figure.caption.18}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:supp_bout_threshold}{{9}{21}{Supplementary Figure S2. Sensitivity of home 6MWD prediction MAE to the minimum walking-bout duration threshold. At each threshold (10, 30, 60, 120, 240 s) the cached per-bout features are filtered, re-aggregated, combined with the 29 whole-recording activity features, and fed to the headline Bout+Act-Top20+Demo pipeline (Ridge $\alpha =20$, leave-one-out cross-validation). Error bars are 95\% percentile bootstrap confidence intervals (B = 2000). The 10\,s threshold yields the best MAE of 56.0\,m; stricter thresholds reduce the number of usable bouts (mean bouts per subject drop from 1{,}454 at 10\,s to 11 at 240\,s) and at 240\,s leave 9 of 101 subjects with zero bouts, degrading MAE to 65.5\,m.\relax }{figure.caption.18}{}}
